        },
        {
            "content_html": "<img src=\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/105274?u=173310b843e2751843265438af8cfb79eda02039&v=4\" width=\"64\" height=\"64\" alt=\"\"/><br/><h3 dir=\"auto\">Moves SVG guides, and reference into subfolders</h3>\n<div class=\"highlight highlight-source-diff notranslate position-relative overflow-auto\" dir=\"auto\" data-snippet-clipboard-copy-content=\"- svg/applying_svg_effects_to_html_content/index.md\n+ svg/guides/applying_svg_effects_to_html_content/index.md\n\n- svg/attribute/accent-height/index.md\n+ svg/reference/attribute/accent-height/index.md\"><pre class=\"notranslate\"><span class=\"pl-md\"><span class=\"pl-md\">-</span> svg/applying_svg_effects_to_html_content/index.md</span>\n<span class=\"pl-mi1\"><span class=\"pl-mi1\">+</span> svg/guides/applying_svg_effects_to_html_content/index.md</span>\n\n<span class=\"pl-md\"><span class=\"pl-md\">-</span> svg/attribute/accent-height/index.md</span>\n<span class=\"pl-mi1\"><span class=\"pl-mi1\">+</span> svg/reference/attribute/accent-height/index.md</span></pre></div>\n<h3 dir=\"auto\">Groups the loose guide into a tutorial</h3>\n<div class=\"highlight highlight-source-diff notranslate position-relative overflow-auto\" dir=\"auto\" data-snippet-clipboard-copy-content=\"- svg/basic_shapes/index.md\n+ svg/tutorials/svg_from_scratch/index.md\n+ svg/tutorials/svg_from_scratch/basic_shapes/index.md\"><pre class=\"notranslate\"><span class=\"pl-md\"><span class=\"pl-md\">-</span> svg/basic_shapes/index.md</span>\n<span class=\"pl-mi1\"><span class=\"pl-mi1\">+</span> svg/tutorials/svg_from_scratch/index.md</span>\n<span class=\"pl-mi1\"><span class=\"pl-mi1\">+</span> svg/tutorials/svg_from_scratch/basic_shapes/index.md</span></pre></div>\n<h3 dir=\"auto\">Creates a landing page for tutorials, guides, and reference</h3>\n<div class=\"highlight highlight-source-diff notranslate position-relative overflow-auto\" dir=\"auto\" data-snippet-clipboard-copy-content=\"+ svg/tutorials/index.md\n+ svg/guides/index.md\n+ svg/reference/index.md\"><pre class=\"notranslate\"><span class=\"pl-mi1\"><span class=\"pl-mi1\">+</span> svg/tutorials/index.md</span>\n<span class=\"pl-mi1\"><span class=\"pl-mi1\">+</span> svg/guides/index.md</span>\n<span class=\"pl-mi1\"><span class=\"pl-mi1\">+</span> svg/reference/index.md</span></pre></div>\n<h3 dir=\"auto\">Uses front-matter sidebar</h3>\n<div class=\"highlight highlight-source-diff notranslate position-relative overflow-auto\" dir=\"auto\" data-snippet-clipboard-copy-content=\"- {{SVGRef}}\n+ sidebar: svgref\"><pre class=\"notranslate\"><span class=\"pl-md\"><span class=\"pl-md\">-</span> {{SVGRef}}</span>\n<span class=\"pl-mi1\"><span class=\"pl-mi1\">+</span> sidebar: svgref</span></pre></div>\n<h3 dir=\"auto\">Motivation</h3>\n<p dir=\"auto\">Docs IA &amp; maintenance, see <a class=\"issue-link js-issue-link\" data-error-text=\"Failed to load title\" data-id=\"2857789700\" data-permission-text=\"Title is private\" data-url=\"https://github.com/mdn/mdn/issues/637\" data-hovercard-type=\"issue\" data-hovercard-url=\"/mdn/mdn/issues/637/hovercard\" href=\"https://github.com/mdn/mdn/issues/637\">mdn/mdn#637</a></p>",
            "url": "https://github.com/mdn/content/pull/38589",
            "title": "Organize SVG into Tutorials, Guides, and Reference",
            "date_modified": "2025-03-14T15:18:38.000Z",
            "date_published": "2025-03-12T13:04:41.000Z",
            "author": {
                "name": "pepelsbey",
                "url": "https://github.com/pepelsbey"
            }
        },
        {
            "content_html": "<img src=\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/495429?u=2f3b9dd03c6c4a961d44a632fe1976c73fa19e1f&v=4\" width=\"64\" height=\"64\" alt=\"\"/><br/>\n<h3 dir=\"auto\">Description</h3>\n<p dir=\"auto\">Updates the non-standard disclaimer.</p>\n<h3 dir=\"auto\">Motivation</h3>\n<p dir=\"auto\">See: <a class=\"issue-link js-issue-link\" data-error-text=\"Failed to load title\" data-id=\"1930153232\" data-permission-text=\"Title is private\" data-url=\"https://github.com/mdn/yari/issues/9774\" data-hovercard-type=\"issue\" data-hovercard-url=\"/mdn/yari/issues/9774/hovercard\" href=\"https://github.com/mdn/yari/issues/9774#issue-1930153232\">mdn/yari#9774 (comment)</a></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p dir=\"auto\">The non-standard disclaimer makes a <strong>valid</strong> point, but also the <strong>wrong discouragement</strong>; designing a website to be exactly the same for all browsers, which may have different default behavior, has never been a valid stance.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<h3 dir=\"auto\">Additional details</h3>\n\n<h3 dir=\"auto\">Related issues and pull requests</h3>\n<p dir=\"auto\">Port from <a class=\"issue-link js-issue-link\" data-error-text=\"Failed to load title\" data-id=\"2305985983\" data-permission-text=\"Title is private\" data-url=\"https://github.com/mdn/yari/issues/11163\" data-hovercard-type=\"pull_request\" data-hovercard-url=\"/mdn/yari/pull/11163/hovercard\" href=\"https://github.com/mdn/yari/pull/11163\">mdn/yari#11163</a>.</p>\n<p dir=\"auto\"><span class=\"issue-keyword tooltipped tooltipped-se\" aria-label=\"This pull request closes issue #9774.\">Fixes</span> <a class=\"issue-link js-issue-link\" data-error-text=\"Failed to load title\" data-id=\"1930153232\" data-permission-text=\"Title is private\" data-url=\"https://github.com/mdn/yari/issues/9774\" data-hovercard-type=\"issue\" data-hovercard-url=\"/mdn/yari/issues/9774/hovercard\" href=\"https://github.com/mdn/yari/issues/9774\">mdn/yari#9774</a>.</p>",
            "url": "https://github.com/mdn/content/pull/38588",
            "title": "Update non-standard disclaimer",
            "date_modified": "2025-03-14T12:56:48.000Z",
            "date_published": "2025-03-12T13:01:11.000Z",
            "author": {
                "name": "caugner",
                "url": "https://github.com/caugner"
            }
        },
        {
            "content_html": "<img src=\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/213073?u=03328c92e96f5d87fa7eea25d9320bcfda3ab8fe&v=4\" width=\"64\" height=\"64\" alt=\"\"/><br/><p dir=\"auto\">This was renamed at the CSSWG <a class=\"issue-link js-issue-link\" data-error-text=\"Failed to load title\" data-id=\"2829071658\" data-permission-text=\"Title is private\" data-url=\"https://github.com/w3c/csswg-drafts/issues/11645\" data-hovercard-type=\"issue\" data-hovercard-url=\"/w3c/csswg-drafts/issues/11645/hovercard?comment_id=2701601350&amp;comment_type=issue_comment\" href=\"https://github.com/w3c/csswg-drafts/issues/11645#issuecomment-2701601350\">w3c/csswg-drafts#11645 (comment)</a> and the change landed in Chrome <code class=\"notranslate\">136.0.7062.0</code> in <a href=\"https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/6333420\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/6333420</a>.</p>\n<p dir=\"auto\">I am not sure on the following though:</p>\n<ul dir=\"auto\">\n<li>How to communicate that <code class=\"notranslate\">raw-string</code> only works from Chrome 136 onwards? BCD would need to reflect that, I guess?</li>\n<li>There is no real explanation what the difference between a CSS string and a CSS <code class=\"notranslate\">&lt;string&gt;</code> is, but I believe that could be part of <a href=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/CSS_Values_and_Units/CSS_data_types\" rel=\"nofollow\">the page on CSS data types</a>.</li>\n</ul>\n<p dir=\"auto\">There is also a drive-by commit that describes how <code class=\"notranslate\">*</code> behaves, as that is related to the use of <code class=\"notranslate\">raw-string</code> vs <code class=\"notranslate\">&lt;string&gt;</code></p>",
            "url": "https://github.com/mdn/content/pull/38580",
            "title": "CSS `attr()`: Rename `string` to `raw-string`",
            "date_modified": "2025-03-11T16:08:51.000Z",
            "date_published": "2025-03-11T16:01:30.000Z",
            "author": {
                "name": "bramus",
                "url": "https://github.com/bramus"
            }
        },
        {
            "content_html": "<img src=\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/184509749?u=32c99471cd8428b224f0459fc5d010064e06e9d3&v=4\" width=\"64\" height=\"64\" alt=\"\"/><br/>\n<h3 dir=\"auto\">Description</h3>\n\n<p dir=\"auto\">Updated the &lt;!doctype html&gt; declaration to  in the HTML Code Style Guide to align with standard conventions and best practices.</p>\n<h3 dir=\"auto\">Motivation</h3>\n\n<p dir=\"auto\">The uppercase  is the widely accepted format for declaring the document type in HTML5. Ensuring consistency helps avoid confusion among readers and follows best coding practices.</p>\n",
            "url": "https://github.com/mdn/content/pull/38578",
            "title": "Mention lowercase doctype in style guide",
            "date_modified": "2025-03-13T17:24:43.000Z",
            "date_published": "2025-03-11T14:00:39.000Z",
            "author": {
                "name": "Ipshita29",
                "url": "https://github.com/Ipshita29"
            }
        },
        {
            "content_html": "<img src=\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/20535393?u=0b527d94715abca32a412b4a4e5672849772536f&v=4\" width=\"64\" height=\"64\" alt=\"\"/><br/>\n<h3 dir=\"auto\">Description</h3>\n\n<p dir=\"auto\">MDN has three lists that enumerate all CSS pseudo-classes, but none of the lists include all pesudo-classes. I have added the missing pseudo-classes to all three lists.</p>\n<p dir=\"auto\">I have also made some minor tweaks:</p>\n<ul dir=\"auto\">\n<li>edited the spec links because the old spec links were incorrect.</li>\n<li>moved a few pesudo-classes around because they were not in alphabetical order.</li>\n<li>removed/added the <code class=\"notranslate\">experimental</code> icon from pesudo-classes where it was incorrect.</li>\n<li>edited the descriptions of <code class=\"notranslate\">:playing</code> and <code class=\"notranslate\">:paused</code> because they were very long and incorrect.</li>\n<li>edited the names and links of a few pseudo-classes that had incorrect names or links.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 dir=\"auto\">Motivation</h3>\n\n<p dir=\"auto\">The lists are confusing and misleading when they are incomplete.</p>\n<h3 dir=\"auto\">Additional details</h3>\n\n<p dir=\"auto\">A few of the new pseudo-classes do not link anywhere because MDN does not have a page for that pseudo-element. I tried to add the link anyways because I expect that the pages will be added in the future, but then the links are redirected to other pseudo-classes that start with the same letters. I think that would create a bad user experience, so I have opted to not add any links instead.</p>\n<h3 dir=\"auto\">Related issues and pull requests</h3>\n\n\n\n",
